We are given an array as input we can perform intialize operation or calculate sum operation for the given range.

when a range is given we compute the sum of the given range.

Algorithm:

step 1 : Initialize step creates and array with holds prefix sums of all the elements.
step 2 : now when ever sumRange is called we check if left index is greater then zero:
                                                                  if true in that case we have to compute sum in the mid of the array so we have to remove prefix sum before left from prefix sum at right
                                                                  else we return prefixSum at index right

Code:
class NumArray {
      int[] prefix;

    public NumArray(int[] nums) {

        prefix = new int[nums.length];
        int sum =0;

        for(int i = 0;i< nums.length; i++)
        {
            sum += nums[i];
            prefix[i] = sum;
        }
        
    }
    
    public int sumRange(int left, int right) {
        if( left > 0)
        {
          return prefix[right] - prefix[left -1];
        }
        else return prefix[right];


        
    }
}

